# Cocos Service Introduction

Cocos Creator provides a **Service** panel in the **Menu bar -> Panel**, and developers can quickly integrate services through the **Service** panel for the game.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Usage

- Open the Cocos Creator, choose **Menu bar -> Panel -> Service** to open the **Service** panel. Click the ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) button above the **Service** panel. Select **Dashboard** and go to the [Cocos Account Center](https://auth.cocos.com/#/) to register your user account.

  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

  Create Personal/Company games as needed after account registration is complete:

  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- After the game is created, return to the Cocos Creator **Service** panel and click the ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) button. After selecting **Set Cocos AppID**, jump to the **Set Cocos AppID** panel. Then select the game and click the **Association** button.

  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

  You can create a game by clicking the **Cocos AppID is not found. Click here to create** button to jump to the Cocos Account Center.

- When the AppID setup is complete, it automatically jumps to the **Service** panel, where you can see that the game name and AppID are already displayed at the top left of the panel.

  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

  If you need to switch games, you can click the ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) button again to select **Unlink**. Then go to the **Set Cocos AppID** panel again and re-select the game.

  ![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
